 BY SALIU SALIU OVER 300 schoolboys abducted from Government Science Secondary School, Kankara, last Friday, have finally arrived Katsina State. The students were conveyed into the state amid tight security. The schoolboys, who were said to be happy to be free at last, were escorted by heavily armed security operatives. Governor Aminu Masari had confirmed on Thursday night that 344 boys abducted from the Kankara School had been released. Masari, who claimed that no ransom was paid to release the boys, said the rescued boys were safe at Tsafe area of the state, adding that they would be taken to Kankara on Friday (today). Details laterâ€¦  